b'We know the issues of systemic racism and housing instability need to be addressed head on.

b'We may not be celebrating the way we are used to, but we still celebrate love in all forms. We are pleased to share we have scored 100% on the @humanrightscampaign Index for Corporate Equality for 16 years. We stand with all our LGBTQ+ associates, members and friends! #Pride2020'

b'For us, #onyourside means standing up for what\xe2\x80\x99s right and shining a light on our partners who address economic empowerment, education and housing \xe2\x80\x93 all core issues at the heart of systemic racism. \nIn the coming weeks and beyond, we\xe2\x80\x99re going to use our platforms to highlight these organizations that we are honored to partner with. Our hope is that it will inspire our community to think, act and learn about how to promote racial equality.'

b'Last Friday, our associates came together to collectively and individually take action to fight for racial equality. In addition to $1 million for social justice organizations \xe2\x80\x93 We are committing to prepare additional education and activism resources for employees.'

b'Today we announced a $1 million, multi-year commitment to support local and national programs dedicated to fostering social justice. The multi-year commitment on criminal justice efforts is in addition to Nationwide\xe2\x80\x99s significant and long-held support of initiatives aimed at addressing economic empowerment, education and housing-all core issues at the heart of systemic racism.'

b'Since the tragic death of George Floyd, we\xe2\x80\x99ve taken time to hear from our associates and partners to understand how we, as a family, can make a difference. Today, in partnership with our African American Associate Resource Groups, we will pause to reflect on this moment in history. Our goal is to remember, to take action and to chart a path forward to eliminate racism and discrimination in our country forever. See our Instagram Story to see how you can virtually join us. #onyourside'
